)
values
  ('1369806e-4ea8-5225-af4b-53d528e72fd4'::uuid, 'b248fb0f-5294-57b4-af76-9938cb3f905c'::uuid, 'maak', 'มาก', 'มาก', 'very / a lot', 'mâak', 'daily', 'You''ll hear and read มาก everywhere: ดีมาก (very good), เผ็ดมาก (very spicy), and discount copy that promises a lot.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('134aa101-deb6-53f4-ab45-73b08ff1f542'::uuid, '4497309f-83d5-5cfd-ae20-98d182c44e7a'::uuid, 'dii', 'ดี', 'ดี', 'good', 'dii', 'daily', 'You''ll see ดี inside greetings, reviews, and product copy. It is one of the most reusable positive words in beginner Thai.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('9aa0d234-007d-5705-abe6-013ec5322296'::uuid, '3be425cd-ea3e-5f8a-ab88-b1efae8eb80f'::uuid, 'gin', 'กิน', 'กิน', 'to eat', 'gin', 'food', 'กิน appears everywhere in daily life, from restaurant invitations to questions about what you want to eat.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('e2ffdcfe-2699-53cb-aa90-ef775738a0b3'::uuid, '4de66997-87a5-56cb-a66f-7b2cce6228ed'::uuid, 'talat', 'ตลาด', 'ตลาด', 'market', 'tà-làat', 'place', 'Markets are everywhere in Thailand. You''ll see ตลาด on signs for night markets, floating markets, and neighborhood markets.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('689621ae-0664-5f67-abdf-69572aa9cd01'::uuid, '0afff15b-0b20-53d3-ae86-21d3fe37de52'::uuid, 'bin', 'บิน', 'บิน', 'to fly', 'bin', 'transport', 'บิน appears in airport language, travel offers, and casual talk about planes and trips. It also helps you see how reusable the -ิน frame is.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('89d521e3-4d9b-523d-ac4e-65377bfe9338'::uuid, 'dc5e9698-631e-5ce9-a0da-6c7fb1abd338'::uuid, 'maae', 'แม่', 'แม่', 'mother', 'mâae', 'daily', 'You''ll see แม่ in family words, shop names, and cultural phrases. It also gives you your first look at a vowel written before the consonant.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('c971805c-561a-5000-a9e8-846afac9e80b'::uuid, '5f706588-560c-598f-ab7a-52a47ecb2015'::uuid, 'raan', 'ร้าน', 'ร้าน', 'shop', 'râan', 'place', 'You''ll see ร้าน everywhere: ร้านกาแฟ, ร้านอาหาร, ร้านยา. Learning it early pays off on almost every street.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('8888dcb4-b725-5c58-abe7-96cfcb8ab970'::uuid, 'a85af404-45e0-50ae-a491-e082f54018a8'::uuid, 'chut', 'ชุด', 'ชุด', 'set / combo', 'chút', 'food', 'ชุด shows up in set menus, school uniforms, and clothing signs. On menus, it often means a fixed combo or meal set.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('c7f7eeee-be9c-59ec-a5ca-e993cf2d61c4'::uuid, 'fb4954f1-e326-56e2-a3d1-b4132b60e254'::uuid, 'sip', 'สิบ', 'สิบ', 'ten', 'sìp', 'sign', 'สิบ helps with prices, receipts, and quantity labels. Even one number word gives you real payoff in markets and transit.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('cc47d33e-ee3d-50dc-a6ce-b3d61029996d'::uuid, '489857d0-a162-5afa-a7bb-c797b5761864'::uuid, 'khao', 'ข้าว', 'ข้าว', 'rice', 'khâao', 'food', 'ข้าว is one of the highest-value food words in Thailand. It appears on menus, in meal names, and in everyday conversation.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('c771541d-bc22-55d6-ade9-52b9d986cfe2'::uuid, '6a8b53e3-50a0-5db3-a089-a15c56bc01c6'::uuid, 'moo', 'หมู', 'หมู', 'pork', 'mǔu', 'food', 'หมู is everywhere on Thai menus. It is also the cleanest early example of the leading-ห pattern that learners need sooner rather than later.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('01409ff0-7f6d-54f3-ab1e-8e428d0ca405'::uuid, 'e387c914-ad75-5a7c-a972-cf079418042d'::uuid, 'ahan', 'อาหาร', 'อาหาร', 'food', 'aa-hǎan', 'food', 'อาหาร appears on restaurant signs, food courts, and delivery labels. Once you can read ร้านอาหาร, the street starts feeling more legible.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('d2faba91-170e-5cef-ad0b-7f3a04ac6143'::uuid, '227b7204-c818-5c7c-ad68-654e72285cd6'::uuid, 'phat', 'ผัด', 'ผัด', 'stir-fry', 'phàt', 'food', 'ผัด appears on some of the most common Thai dishes, from ผัดไทย to vegetable stir-fries. It is one of the highest-value cooking words you can learn.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('53cc0560-d985-57a9-a82a-f8647ffb52bf'::uuid, '7158a845-3580-5cfa-a158-db2ec59ba64b'::uuid, 'khong', 'ของ', 'ของ', 'of / belonging to', 'khǎwng', 'daily', 'ของ is one of the most common words in Thai. It links things to owners (ของผม, mine), labels stuff to buy or eat (ของกิน, things to eat), and shows up constantly on signs and menus.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('41ea5980-7420-51d8-a418-5d4411c1c665'::uuid, '3a606423-7c75-5465-a2f4-94d6250f99c8'::uuid, 'thang', 'ทาง', 'ทาง', 'way / direction', 'thaang', 'sign', 'ทาง marks routes and directions on signs everywhere. ทางออก (way out / exit) is one of the most useful sign words you can learn to spot.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('cd23b164-7b20-5878-ae97-35dbb1d4b85f'::uuid, '7282cb0a-aba7-5f75-a56b-f027f905a879'::uuid, 'ja', 'จะ', 'จะ', 'will (future particle)', 'jà', 'daily', 'จะ is a core grammar word placed before a verb to mean something will happen: จะกิน (will eat), จะมา (will come). You''ll read it in countless sentences.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('718088c1-9980-5540-ae97-4a03b319a76e'::uuid, '8df83813-8fd3-546a-a5bd-bf786e534b3b'::uuid, 'kem', 'เกม', 'เกม', 'game', 'geem', 'daily', 'เกม is a loanword you''ll see on phones, arcades, and shopfronts like ร้านเกม (game shop). It''s a clean way to learn how leading vowels work.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('29f69529-8848-57e6-aefc-97277fe6fce5'::uuid, '220e45ef-a665-57fb-af90-9359b64d941b'::uuid, 'gai', 'ไก่', 'ไก่', 'chicken', 'gài', 'food', 'ไก่ means chicken and appears on menus everywhere — ข้าวมันไก่ (chicken rice) is a national favorite. It also teaches the two leading ai vowels.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('0effddc9-d911-5f5a-a5a3-dda9b5454195'::uuid, 'a5eb07e9-b71d-59c8-a3ac-ce5fab1e5fc0'::uuid, 'to', 'โต', 'โต', 'big / to grow', 'dtoo', 'daily', 'โต means big or to grow up. It teaches the leading long-o vowel โ, which — like เ and ไ — is written before the consonant but spoken after it.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('953ff4f2-a5b7-5bda-abe3-51eab2ed86d0'::uuid, 'd1d3fe12-62f5-5fa6-ab64-c59a5156b603'::uuid, 'pit', 'ปิด', 'ปิด', 'closed', 'bpìt', 'sign', 'ปิด (closed) and เปิด (open) are the most useful sign pair in Thailand — on shops, doors, and opening hours. ป is a tight p, easy to confuse with บ.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('b3a09902-4528-5718-a8fe-068c2032b55d'::uuid, '9f1d8410-24a1-50ce-af53-d035634ca0d6'::uuid, 'ya', 'ยา', 'ยา', 'medicine', 'yaa', 'sign', 'ยา means medicine — ร้านขายยา (pharmacy) is a key sign to recognize. ย also closes many words as a y-glide, alongside ว as a w-glide.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('32871dae-effa-553d-a900-ababa15c81cd'::uuid, 'c5e22f76-3e90-52fc-ad0e-83bbb93263af'::uuid, 'khon', 'คน', 'คน', 'person', 'khon', 'daily', 'คน (person) is one of the highest-frequency words in Thai. It opens countless compounds — คนไทย (Thai person), คนขับ (driver) — and shows the low-class partner of the kh sound you met in ข.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('410398be-ab73-5dc2-ae6e-0a2fa60be9a4'::uuid, 'be7bc78d-7bb3-5b03-abd3-d8b659c200cd'::uuid, 'phaeng', 'แพง', 'แพง', 'expensive', 'phaeng', 'sign', 'แพง (expensive) is a core price-tag adjective. It also completes the trio of p letters: ป (bp), ผ (ph, high), and now พ (ph, low).', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('3ca2f3fd-058e-5d41-a635-caf8caa24c00'::uuid, 'ca28d549-96b2-585a-a988-213769cb7801'::uuid, 'nam', 'น้ำ', 'น้ำ', 'water', 'náam', 'daily', 'น้ำ (water) is everywhere — bottles, menus, and compounds like น้ำแข็ง (ice) and น้ำมัน (oil). It introduces ◌ำ, a vowel that carries its own final m.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('72e8b19d-90ec-5161-af69-546c398d3d6e'::uuid, 'e1787c4e-fabf-58a7-ad6e-8a576a895014'::uuid, 'khao-he', 'เขา', 'เขา', 'he / she / they', 'khǎo', 'daily', 'เขา is the everyday pronoun for he, she, or they. It shows how เ and า wrap around a consonant to make the short ao diphthong.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('14c3515c-5502-5cae-a90c-ae4f26f88f1e'::uuid, '32329333-ccf2-5eab-ae0f-bd10a8a64107'::uuid, 'soi', 'ซอย', 'ซอย', 'lane / soi', 'sawy', 'sign', 'ซอย (a lane off a main road) is part of nearly every Thai address. It introduces ซ, the low-class partner of the s sound.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('c308414f-aec6-5570-a935-484457a5e5a9'::uuid, 'ebb4afe8-f2e5-55fd-a790-7687d9b8fdc1'::uuid, 'fai', 'ไฟ', 'ไฟ', 'fire / light', 'fai', 'sign', 'ไฟ means fire, light, or electricity. It powers everyday signs like ไฟฟ้า (electricity) and ไฟแดง (red light), and introduces the low-class f.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('a8707ee0-b48b-524c-a63b-ab2e78e46ba4'::uuid, 'f744f3da-0ec6-5c6d-af0c-4be7bc5d245c'::uuid, 'thanon', 'ถนน', 'ถนน', 'road / street', 'thà-nǒn', 'sign', 'ถนน (road) appears on every street sign. It also shows the leading-consonant rule: the high-class ถ reaches across and sets the tone of the next syllable.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('92514603-9bf0-5e73-a268-56444aa033f0'::uuid, 'c7ea9e7c-9fe6-5f5c-a5f3-67ad2e608fd1'::uuid, 'mue', 'มือ', 'มือ', 'hand', 'mue', 'daily', 'มือ (hand) shows the long ue vowel and its silent อ seat. It builds mobile-age words like มือถือ (mobile phone), literally ''hand-hold''.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('f754213c-ae41-581c-af07-ad5f68b13c45'::uuid, '94181540-937d-5441-ade4-480016067418'::uuid, 'bia', 'เบียร์', 'เบียร์', 'beer', 'biia', 'food', 'เบียร์ (beer) is a loanword that shows two new tools: the ia diphthong and ◌์, the mark that silences a consonant — here the final ร.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('5473971c-c02a-52e1-a21f-05394208afb6'::uuid, 'd6f5428a-b561-54ad-ab67-02d1f274bc9c'::uuid, 'wua', 'วัว', 'วัว', 'cow', 'wuua', 'daily', 'วัว (cow) introduces the ua diphthong. It is a friendly word that also shows how ◌ั teams up with ว to make a gliding vowel.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('dbfcd390-2522-5af1-a8be-1c4158106e14'::uuid, 'e08fd5fc-bed4-5a96-a23b-f8fa42eabe13'::uuid, 'jer', 'เจอ', 'เจอ', 'to meet / to find', 'jer', 'daily', 'เจอ (to meet, to run into) introduces the long er vowel. It is a high-frequency verb — เจอกัน (see you) closes countless conversations.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('9685afb1-3e97-5a92-aa1c-2f04112c19ac'::uuid, 'c1dbe83d-891d-55df-a684-4f9e445b3472'::uuid, 'plaa', 'ปลา', 'ปลา', 'fish', 'bplaa', 'food', 'ปลา (fish) opens with a true cluster, ปล: both consonants blend with no vowel between them. This lesson teaches how clusters differ from the hidden-vowel frame.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('49b4ef3d-663d-5c7d-a495-87b6c22d954b'::uuid, '0f5d0c7d-a70f-56b8-ae86-6c648f7a705e'::uuid, 'toh', 'โต๊ะ', 'โต๊ะ', 'table', 'dtó', 'daily', 'โต๊ะ (table) carries mai tri. With mai chattawa, this lesson completes all four Thai tone marks — the ones that appear mostly on mid-class, loan, and food words.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('935f50f5-c6cd-5254-a0f5-053701c910d9'::uuid, 'd3afacf9-e786-5727-a205-494909843fa8'::uuid, 'khao-news', 'ข่าว', 'ข่าว', 'news', 'khàao', 'sign', 'ข่าว (news) anchors a review of the whole tone system. Here you pull class, tone mark, and syllable type together into one picture.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('b1f339e0-0487-5fa2-a739-0a2371f9675d'::uuid, '909aae5d-bc64-578e-a15d-949af76df637'::uuid, 'dek', 'เด็ก', 'เด็ก', 'child', 'dèk', 'daily', 'เด็ก (child) introduces ◌็ (mai taikhu), a mark that shortens the vowel in a closed syllable without adding any sound of its own.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('fb5f792e-7a1a-58a8-a854-e7272e00726e'::uuid, '3dcf575d-7f9c-50e6-a9f0-da47780674d2'::uuid, 'chaa', 'ช้าๆ', 'ช้าๆ', 'slowly / take it easy', 'cháa-cháa', 'daily', 'ช้าๆ (slowly) shows ◌ๆ (mai yamok), the mark that tells you to say the previous word again — for plurals, emphasis, or ''each and every''.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('b3d306cd-ca0f-5db3-acdd-415d8221003c'::uuid, '975e9228-70a0-58a4-afbb-d00e81532969'::uuid, 'koh', 'เกาะ', 'เกาะ', 'island', 'gàw', 'place', 'เกาะ (island) shows the short partner of the leading vowels. This lesson gathers the short diphthongs and the unwritten short o that hides between two consonants.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('0766d9bf-b229-576f-ae9c-1b34d67f8580'::uuid, '83b7993a-6759-55b2-a99f-d03490796283'::uuid, 'numerals', '๑๐ บาท', '๑๐ บาท', '10 baht', 'sìp bàat', 'sign', 'Thai numerals still appear on temple and park entry signs, dual pricing, license plates, and banknotes. ๑๐ บาท (10 baht) is a typical price you will read.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('59f46d6b-4b42-5198-a4df-d94c4832cee3'::uuid, '4e0ae282-3b97-593c-afae-1564cfe169e8'::uuid, 'krungthep', 'กรุงเทพฯ', 'กรุงเทพฯ', 'Bangkok', 'grung-thêep', 'place', 'กรุงเทพฯ (Bangkok) ends in ฯ (paiyannoi), which stands in for the rest of the city''s ceremonial name. You read the short everyday form aloud.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('ea5c0831-1d72-5d88-a4c8-7083916caf2e'::uuid, '7b6fd017-a364-50db-ab0f-d2ba417b03cf'::uuid, 'chan', 'ฉัน', 'ฉัน', 'I / me', 'chǎn', 'daily', 'ฉัน (I/me) is an everyday pronoun. It introduces two high-class letters: ฉ (ch) and ฝ (f), which complete the aspirate pairs.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('73c521fc-c4c9-5bce-a86e-515ccc4b52d0'::uuid, 'a03fce9c-2e72-5cef-a746-65946b24fa81'::uuid, 'yai', 'ใหญ่', 'ใหญ่', 'big', 'yài', 'daily', 'ใหญ่ (big) uses ญ. This lesson adds four more low-class letters — ญ, ธ, ภ, ฮ — that duplicate sounds you know but appear across everyday and formal words.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('fc785d0a-8d8b-50be-a1de-286e89480957'::uuid, '94c2f1fe-a488-5d78-abef-78729be22427'::uuid, 'prathet', 'ประเทศ', 'ประเทศ', 'country', 'bprà-thêet', 'sign', 'ประเทศ (country) ends in ศ, one of three Sanskrit-derived duplicates. ศ, ษ (both s) and ณ (n) show up in formal vocabulary and on signs.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('f02df751-db9e-5bbc-a06f-546288a18aef'::uuid, '5cf475a5-bf3b-5c84-a6a5-db4e09025c11'::uuid, 'kila', 'กีฬา', 'กีฬา', 'sport(s)', 'gii-laa', 'daily', 'กีฬา (sports) uses the rare ฬ. This recognition lesson gathers eight uncommon Pali/Sanskrit letters that duplicate sounds you already read.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('f47dd5a1-4600-5b0c-aea9-363bfe7efab7'::uuid, '5a17f704-8e6f-5e05-a52f-4edf3bd1a7cf'::uuid, 'angkrit', 'อังกฤษ', 'อังกฤษ', 'England / English', 'ang-grìt', 'sign', 'อังกฤษ (English) shows ฤ, a vowel-like letter read ri, rue, or rer by word. This lesson also gathers the leading-อ words and the silent-r spellings.', '{}'::jsonb),
  ('fafa943c-7a2b-56d3-ae34-bfbea63ef035'::uuid, '7a7728f1-ad4d-565b-a8ce-96abcf166817'::uuid, 'khuat-archaic', 'ฃวด', 'ฃวด', 'bottle (archaic spelling of ขวด)', 'khùuat', 'daily', 'ฃวด is an old spelling of ขวด (bottle) using the obsolete ฃ. This closing lesson is recognition only: these glyphs no longer appear in modern Thai writing.', '{}'::jsonb);

